I shared a few quick thoughts on becoming a mom in my newsletter. Thanks to all the lovely readers who left such nice notes and shared your own stories. After I hit publish, I confided in my husband that I wasn't sure how much more writing about my own life I could continue to do. Writing about myself feels vulnerable and silly, but knowing it reaches so many people who find value and connection through it is a huge relief! You can read the whole thing at downtime.substack.com.

This romcom was such a treat! It’s a reimagining of “When Harry Met Sally.” The witty and hilarious banter stood out to me in this book - I had to look up the author to see if she’s a comedian IRL like one of her characters (she is not). If you like your characters with a bit of an edge, love books set in New York City, and want some good fall vibes, pick this one up. (I listened to it on audio - through many night time feedings - and it was really well done.) Also, I’d be surprised if it’s not picked up for TV. Did anyone else get that sense? #youagainbykategoldbeck #bookstagram

I've gone through many challenging transitions before, but the past few weeks of returning to work have been among the most difficult by far. This isn't necessarily due to my workload or lack of time—those things are present, yes, but I can grapple with them. I've found that the difficulty stems from how I'm responding to my new reality: being impatient with myself and silently berating myself for not doing more as a working mom. (Even just now, I thought, "I feel like a mess. I haven't done my hair, and I'm not wearing real pants." But HELLO?! I woke up at midnight, 4am, and 6am with the 👶. Give yourself some grace, sheeeeesh.)⁠
⁠
I shared some of my goals for 2024 in my latest newsletter, and needless to say, one of them is to be nicer to myself and practice more self-compassion. My other big goal touches on community, and there are so many great comments and ideas in this one from readers! You can see the post and comments at downtime.substack.com to get some inspo.
Happy snow day! And end of a long week! ❄️🥰🥶🧤
